{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17623549","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17623549"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T16:12:11+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T16:12:11+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16870"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16870","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16870"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.07,0.67,0.09,0.09,0.09]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9560"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"68657"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9560","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9560"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16870"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"54114"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"8427"},{"type":"tags","id":"9883"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22577"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22579"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"68657","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/68657"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EEndothelin is an important regulator of vascular tone produced by the endothelium.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the primary physiological action of endothelin-1?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Stimulates prostacyclin release","Causes potent vasoconstriction","Inhibits platelet aggregation","Promotes vasodilation","Increases vascular permeability"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EEndothelin-1 is a potent vasoconstrictor peptide. When released by endothelial cells, it binds primarily to ETA receptors on vascular smooth muscle cells to cause \u003Cstrong\u003Epotent vasoconstriction\u003C/strong\u003E through calcium-dependent mechanisms.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPromotes vasodilation\u003C/strong\u003E - Endothelin causes vasoconstriction, not vasodilation. Nitric oxide is the main vasodilator produced by endothelium\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInhibits platelet aggregation\u003C/strong\u003E - This is a function of prostacyclin, not endothelin\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStimulates prostacyclin release\u003C/strong\u003E - While endothelin can have some effects on other mediators, this is not its primary action\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreases vascular permeability\u003C/strong\u003E - Primarily mediated by histamine and bradykinin (inflammatory markers)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEndothelin production is increased by various stimuli including hypoxia, shear stress, and inflammatory mediators. Its potent vasoconstrictive effects make it an important therapeutic target in conditions like pulmonary hypertension - for example, by the endothelin receptor antagonist medication Bosentan. \u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Endothelin-1 is a potent vasoconstrictor peptide produced by vascular endothelial cells.","Endothelin production is stimulated by hypoxia, shear stress, and various inflammatory mediators."],"references":["Asbury, C., Rieke, F., Hille, B., Bothwell, M., \u0026 Tuthill, J. (2023) Physiology. Simple Book Publishing. https://uw.pressbooks.pub/physiology/."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"54114"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16870"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"54114","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/54114"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-10T09:07:00+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-10T09:07:00+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9560"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"68657"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4926","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4926"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec0","name":"Cardiovascular","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2024-10-17T23:14:59+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-31T09:50:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"13"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemC